article.headline: Bryant 24, Wagner 14
article.story: NEW YORK -- Adam Farnsworth threw an 80-yard touchdown pass to Pete Zagorski in the first quarter and Bryant went on to beat Wagner 24-14 on Saturday. After Anthony Castelli returned a blocked punt 4 yards for a score to tie the game at 7 for Wagner (2-2) in the first quarter, the Bulldogs (3-2) took the lead for good on a 4-yard run by Lindsey Gamble. Jay Graber threw a 7-yard touchdown pass to Anthony Dinaso at 10:51 of the third quarter to make it 24-7 for Bryant. Farnsworth finished 9-for-18 for 124 yards.
